{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/61228", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/61228/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/61228/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/61228/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/61228", "id": 448676179, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU0NDg2NzYxNzk=", "number": 61228, "title": "RwLock doesn't work fine with `if let` statement", "user": {"login": "hicqu", "id": 8407317, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjg0MDczMTc=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/8407317?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/hicqu", "html_url": "https://github.com/hicqu", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/hicqu/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/hicqu/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/hicqu/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/hicqu/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/hicqu/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/hicqu/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/hicqu/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/hicqu/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/hicqu/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 5, "created_at": "2019-05-27T05:47:52Z", "updated_at": "2019-06-04T00:44:54Z", "closed_at": "2019-06-04T00:44:54Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Here is a code example:\r\n```rust\r\nuse std::sync::RwLock;\r\nfn main() {\r\n    let x = RwLock::new(None);\r\n    if let Some(xx) = x.read().unwrap().as_ref() {\r\n        println!(\"x is {}\", xx);\r\n    } else {\r\n        let mut xx = x.write().unwrap();\r\n        *xx = Some(100i32);\r\n    }\r\n    println!(\"Hello, world!\");\r\n}\r\n```\r\nAs my expected it should print \"hello, world\" but it doesn't when I run it.\r\nI guess the reason is the `read guard` is not dropped correctly in `else branch`.\r\n\r\nI have tested it with \r\n```\r\nnightly-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu (default)\r\nrustc 1.36.0-nightly (3991285f5 2019-04-25)\r\n```\r\nand\r\n```\r\nstable-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu (default)\r\nrustc 1.34.1 (fc50f328b 2019-04-24)\r\n```\r\nThe results are same.\r\n\r\nAfter I change the code to\r\n```rust\r\nuse std::sync::RwLock;\r\nfn main() {\r\n    let x = RwLock::new(None);\r\n    let x_guard = x.read().unwrap();\r\n    if let Some(xx) = x_guard.as_ref() {\r\n        println!(\"x is {}\", xx);\r\n    } else {\r\n        drop(x_guard);\r\n        let mut xx = x.write().unwrap();\r\n        *xx = Some(100i32);\r\n    }\r\n    println!(\"Hello, world!\");\r\n}\r\n```\r\nWe can get the correct result now.", "closed_by": {"login": "Mark-Simulacrum", "id": 5047365, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjUwNDczNjU=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5047365?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum", "html_url": "https://github.com/Mark-Simulacrum", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/user